OL,3,CO'Dowd halts business rates process
OL,4,Cafter hospitality backlash
OL,6,F"Hospitality stands ready to play its
OL,7,Fpart; we now await the minister's next
OL,8,Fsteps and further clarity on what this
OL,9,Fmeans for our industry."
OL,11,FUlster Unionist economy spokesperson
OL,12,FDiana Armstrong said it was a
OL,13,F"climbdown" by Mr O'Dowd.
OL,15,FShe said: "The minister must now
OL,16,Fexplain why he failed to intervene at
OL,17,Fan earlier stage to recognise the
OL,18,Fdevastating impact these punishing
OL,19,Frate increases would have on core
OL,20,Fhospitality providers, including
OL,21,Fhotels, pubs, and food outlets.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@XO]uD@AOUuD@KO]wD@KOU
